<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I don't see the big deal with giving clarity to people... i mean, it's only what? 80 mana?  I was soloing East Karana guards for a while (before they got super buffed) and I would shout "giving clarity out at the bridge for the next 3 minutes) I mean, isn't the whole point of the game social interaction?  I made lots of friends giving out clarity (many of whom were twinks and had other characters on the server who i could group with later on)  I could give 10 people clarity and lose only like a bar and a half of mana, which is nothing to gain back since naturally i have clarity cast on myself too.  I never charge for clarity, ever.  Sometimes people will cast SOW on me in return, which is kind of annoying because i have journeyman boots, and SOW always seems to run out at the most inopportune moments.  But, really, clarity was given to us to help others out, which is what we should use it for without complaining.  I think you can find the 1 minute in your busy EQ life to cast a few claritys and then gain back the mana.<p>

Autumn Blight, 38 Enchanter, Prexus</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
