<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">There are times I may be going thru a zone and stop and cast Clarity on all the caster types (i.e. the Orc Side of Highpass) I feel this is a friendly thing to do and some people even ask what the spell does.. so in that aspect it is refreshing to introduce some players about this wonderful spell.  One thing does bother me tho... I constantly get tells on a daily basis from some of these recipients for clarity (seems as if they have a hotkey and hit it often til I log on). This can be very annoying since there are times I am either in a /tell conversation using the /r for reply and lose the long-named person or am fighting/conversing in a room half way acroos Norrath. All this amounts to is "buff begging". People that cast clarity or sow don't "owe" it to EVERYONE ALL THE TIME. Consider it a friendly gesture and continue on with your own game-playing.  It's the person who constantly harasses some of us that makes us not want to do it anymore. If you happen to be one of those people and are reading this,  please understand that people do not log on the game to do nothing and buff people for the couple hours at night after a hard days work. We too would like to enjoy the game. Take what you get as a gift and be thankful.<p>

People on the Lanys T'vyl server will tell you that I still will stop and dole out the drug occasionally... so I am not saying I won't do it anymore "yet". But a few more spammin "buff-beggars" may make me soon either charge or stop altogether.<p>

Be safe and enjoy the drug!<br>
Bazuzu, level 38 Enchanter<br>
Lanys T'vyl server</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
